        },
        "subheading_CpjCgq": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Using the touch surface"
          }
        },
        "text_JA9R9B": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The Pulse uses a capacitive touch surface to register your inputs. For best reliability, follow these tips:</p><ul><li>Always use two fingers placed flat across the surface. Do not use just your fingertips.</li><li>Touch the surface briefly for each tap.</li><li>Make sure you are wearing the device when using the touch surface. The sensor works best when it is in contact with your skin.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "image_7Y7ixP": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Pulse_Order_4_ac48260d-15ec-422f-bce3-0e1683293932.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_N6Tqzk": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_nncB99": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Powering it on and off"
          }
        },
        "text_qQwfnp": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To power your Pulse on or off, twist the ring at least 1/4 turn in either direction, then hold the touch surface with two fingers for two seconds. Make sure you are wearing the device before powering it on.</p><p>The soundwave light stays on while the device is powered. After you finish playing, power off your Pulse using the same procedure.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_hPgcxR": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Pulse_Order_5_b00c077e-ed5f-4720-9e92-23e5990d60e2.jpg"
          }
