        "heading_pbekez": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How to feel the beat"
          }
        },
        "text_EAFjAi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Using a vibrational metronome feels different at first. When you start using Pulse, give yourself some time to get used to it. Don’t give up. You will improve with practice, just like when learning to use a traditional metronome.</p><p>Over time, the vibration can become a subconscious cue that helps you keep the beat without thinking about it.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_tjcndY": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_7eTcFU": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Using the companion app"
          }
        },
        "text_3dDnyy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Because every musician is different, you can customize Pulse to your preferences using our app.</p><p>To customize or turn off the lights and vibrations, open the mobile app and go to <strong>Settings → Pulse settings → Lights</strong> or <strong>Vibrations</strong>. Try different vibration intensities and durations to find what works best for you.</p><p>For more information on how to use the app, refer to the app manual.</p>"
          }
        },
        "button_NGjw3K": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "label": "View app manual",
            "button_size": "large",
            "icon_position": "none",
            "link": "shopify://pages/manual-the-metronome-app"
          }
        },
        "image_HAitk8": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Pulse_Order_11.jpg"
